    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, very fine) were evaluated for construct stiffness and von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction. Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI). Results demonstrated that the medium mesh (element edge length ≤ 0.4 mm at critical regions) achieved a GCI below 1.2% for all three QoIs, confirming discretization error within acceptable bounds. The study was executed in Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 with quadratic tetrahedral elements (SOLID187).",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
